00:23:33,900 --> 00:23:35,490
你好 初次见面
Hello. Nice to meet you.

362
00:23:35,570 --> 00:23:37,320
我确实是第一次见到你
I am meeting you for the first time,

363
00:23:38,030 --> 00:23:39,870
但我一点都不好
but it isn't nice for me.

364
00:23:39,950 --> 00:23:41,870
看来是这样
Oh, you're right.

365
00:23:42,460 --> 00:23:43,370
我在开玩笑
I'm just kidding.

366
00:23:48,210 --> 00:23:50,130
看来我当时帮你还是值得的
It did pay off to help you out back then.

367
00:23:50,710 --> 00:23:53,880
我们还没有决定要接这个案子
We haven't decided to take on your case yet.

368
00:23:53,970 --> 00:23:57,680
但你们都来这里了 就说明还是有机会
But the fact that you came all the way here means there's a chance.

369
00:23:59,010 --> 00:24:02,180
剩下的就看我如何回答了
The rest is left to how I answer.

370
00:24:02,850 --> 00:24:03,850
是吧
Isn't that right?

371
00:24:04,600 --> 00:24:06,100
没错 你说对了
That's about right.

372
00:24:07,770 --> 00:24:10,940
你的双亲去世了 你不难过吗
Both of your parents died. Aren't you sad?

373
00:24:11,570 --> 00:24:13,110
我一定要难过吗
Do I have to be sad?

374
00:24:15,820 --> 00:24:18,320
而且不是双亲 是其中一位吧
It isn't both of them. Isn't it just one of them?

375
00:24:18,820 --> 00:24:21,540
我爸还没被发现 所以他还是失踪状态
My father hasn't been found yet, so he's missing.

376
00:24:22,040 --> 00:24:23,870
我听说你主张自己无罪
I heard you claim innocence.

377
00:24:23,950 --> 00:24:25,460
不是主张 是事实
It's not a claim, it's the truth.

378
00:24:26,040 --> 00:24:29,790
检方说我遗弃了我爸的尸体
The prosecution says I disposed of my father's dead body…

379
00:24:31,750 --> 00:24:33,800
并对我妈做了那种事
and did that to my mother,

380
00:24:34,470 --> 00:24:36,260
但我只是洗了个澡
but I was simply taking a bath.

381
00:24:36,340 --> 00:24:38,800
我也不知道楼下当时发生了什么事
I didn't know what was going on downstairs.

382
00:24:39,800 --> 00:24:43,560
如果知道 我还会洗澡吗
If I had known, do you think I would've taken a bath?

383
00:24:44,980 --> 00:24:46,350
还是泡泡浴
A bubble bath at that?

384
00:24:46,440 --> 00:24:49,190
那个时间洗泡泡浴也不是常有的事
It doesn't seem normal to take a bubble bath at that hour either.

385
00:24:49,270 --> 00:24:52,190
就算不是常有的事 也不能说明是我做的啊
Just because it isn't normal doesn't mean it's a crime.

386
00:24:53,400 --> 00:24:57,780
那你认为杀死你母亲的人是谁呢
Then, Mr. Kim, who do you think did that to your mother?

387
00:25:00,990 --> 00:25:02,740
消失的父亲
My missing father.

388
00:25:06,960 --> 00:25:08,870
他俩平时关系就不好
The two didn't get along.

389
00:25:08,960 --> 00:25:11,670
你和他们的关系也不好 不是吗
You didn't get along with them either, did you?

390
00:25:15,670 --> 00:25:18,510
我很期待能够见到律师
I was looking forward to meeting my lawyer.

391
00:25:20,510 --> 00:25:22,430
但今天来的好像是检察官
But it feels like a prosecutor is here.

392
00:25:23,010 --> 00:25:24,970
很抱歉 其实
I'm sorry. Actually,

393
00:25:25,060 --> 00:25:27,100
我们来这里是有很重要的原因
there's a particular reason why we came here.

394
00:25:27,890 --> 00:25:31,400
白法律事务所的级别 和我们律所的差距很大
There's a huge gap between Law Firm Baek and our office.

395
00:25:31,480 --> 00:25:33,900
你为什么要委托给我们
Why do you want us to represent you?

396
00:25:33,980 --> 00:25:36,610
他们规模很大 收费又高 我以为很有实力
I thought they'd be good because they're big and expensive,

397
00:25:36,690 --> 00:25:37,900
但其实没什么能耐
but they weren't so impressive.

398
00:25:39,150 --> 00:25:40,200
他们只会看眼色
They kept minding others.

399
00:25:42,620 --> 00:25:44,540
他们说要放弃辩护 我就同意了
They wanted to withdraw, so I told them to do so.

400
00:25:44,620 --> 00:25:45,870
所以呢
So?

401
00:25:45,950 --> 00:25:49,000
我也想过找其他律所
I thought about hiring another law firm,

402
00:25:49,080 --> 00:25:51,920
但可能会让人觉得 我在试图用钱逃避罪行
but it might appear as though I'm getting away with it using my money.

403
00:25:53,000 --> 00:25:56,760
在寻找的过程中 我想起了你
While I was searching for one, you came to my mind.

404
00:25:56,840 --> 00:25:58,380
好 然后呢
Okay, and?

405
00:26:03,640 --> 00:26:04,720
就这些吗
Is that all?

406
00:26:05,310 --> 00:26:06,970
你找律师也太随意了吧
You aren't putting much effort into it.

407
00:26:07,640 --> 00:26:09,440
如果败诉 你可能就无法被释放了
You may not be released if you lose the trial.

408
00:26:10,520 --> 00:26:13,020
你找律师应该更慎重些
You should be more careful about hiring a lawyer.

409
00:26:14,900 --> 00:26:16,280
但我是无辜的
But I'm not guilty.

410
00:26:18,150 --> 00:26:19,820
我为什么要担心那些
Why would I worry about that?

411
00:26:22,410 --> 00:26:23,570
难道不是吗
Don't you think so?

412
00:26:28,500 --> 00:26:30,330
你不觉得他让人毛骨悚然吗
Doesn't he seem rather creepy?

413
00:26:30,750 --> 00:26:31,870
哪方面
What do you mean?

414
00:26:32,460 --> 00:26:35,340
没什么 他看起来一点都不冤枉
Well, he doesn't act like he was wrongfully charged.

415
00:26:35,840 --> 00:26:39,170
在这种情况下 他却表现得游刃有余
It's odd that he is so relaxed in a situation like this.

416
00:26:40,050 --> 00:26:41,590
他看起来也很会动脑筋
And he seems pretty clever.

417
00:26:49,520 --> 00:26:50,810
你不会接的吧
You won't take it, right?

418
00:26:52,600 --> 00:26:54,610
你的疑惑已经解开了吧
You've got all your answers.

419
00:26:54,770 --> 00:26:57,150
我们再去一个地方吧 我还想了解一些事
Let's drop by one more place. I need to figure something out.

420
00:26:58,730 --> 00:27:01,200
你还要去哪里
Where are we going now? Hey.

421
00:27:01,610 --> 00:27:02,740
千律师
Mr. Cheon.

422
00:27:04,280 --> 00:27:06,490
白法律事务所

423
00:27:12,290 --> 00:27:13,580
你来这里干吗
Why do you want to go here?

424
00:27:15,130 --> 00:27:16,790
他们可是退出了此案
This law firm withdrew from this case.

425
00:27:16,880 --> 00:27:18,550
我想当面问他们一些事
I have to ask them something in person.

426
00:27:20,460 --> 00:27:22,760
那你有预约吗 你至少要先预约吧
Did you make an appointment? You should make one first.

427
00:27:22,840 --> 00:27:24,680
好 我现在就去见他们 然后预约
Sure. I'll make one when I see them.

428
00:27:26,140 --> 00:27:28,890
哪有人见面再预约的
Who makes an appointment when they see the person?

429
00:27:29,470 --> 00:27:30,560
在这里
Right here.

430
00:27:32,480 --> 00:27:34,230
我快疯了
He's driving me insane.

431
00:27:39,400 --> 00:27:40,570
白实习
Ms. Baek.

432
00:27:41,440 --> 00:27:43,450
你在干吗 我们快走吧
What are you doing? Let's get going.

433
00:27:49,200 --> 00:27:51,080
判决已经出来了
It was ruled as unconstitutional,

434
00:27:51,160 --> 00:27:54,290
所以请大家充分准备好 相关资料和案例
so please thoroughly search for related materials and instances.

435
00:27:55,080 --> 00:27:56,420
-好的 -好的
Yes, sir.

436
00:28:01,630 --> 00:28:03,840
有位叫千智勋的律师来访
A lawyer called Cheon Jihun is here to see you.

437
00:28:04,220 --> 00:28:07,010
我们现在在开会 你让他下次约好再来
We're in a meeting, so tell him to make an appointment next time.

438
00:28:07,090 --> 00:28:08,390
不了
No.

439
00:28:09,050 --> 00:28:10,680
让他进来吧
Let him in.

440
00:28:10,760 --> 00:28:12,020
什么
Pardon?

441
00:28:12,600 --> 00:28:14,730
我们休息一会儿吧
Let's take a brief break.

442
00:28:16,600 --> 00:28:17,810
休息一会儿吧
Let's take a break.

443
00:28:17,900 --> 00:28:19,190
好久不见
It's been a long time, sir.

444
00:28:19,270 --> 00:28:21,280
是啊 好久不见
Yes, it has been a long time.

445
00:28:21,940 --> 00:28:23,530
假装你不认识我
Pretend you don't know me.

446
00:28:33,620 --> 00:28:36,250
这位是我的实习生 白实习 快打声招呼
Oh, this is my probationary employee. Ms. Baek, say hello to them.

447
00:28:36,330 --> 00:28:39,630
你好 初次见面 我是白玛丽
Hello. Let me greet you. I'm Baek Mari.

448
00:28:39,710 --> 00:28:41,040
很高兴见到你
Nice to meet you.

449
00:28:41,130 --> 00:28:42,670
我也很高兴
Nice to meet you too.

450
00:28:44,130 --> 00:28:46,430
不过请问有什么事
Anyway, what brings you here?

451
00:28:47,380 --> 00:28:51,560
我听说你放弃了枫津洞案的辩护
I heard you withdrew from representing the Pungjin-dong case.

452
00:28:52,430 --> 00:28:55,600
是的 这有什么问题吗
Yes, is there a problem with that?

453
00:28:55,680 --> 00:28:57,230
我在考虑接这个案子
I thought I'd take that case.

454
00:28:58,020 --> 00:28:59,940
-千律师 -怎么了
-Mr. Cheon. -Yes?

455
00:29:01,730 --> 00:29:03,650
看来你打算接一件困难的案子
You're about to take on a difficult case.

456
00:29:03,730 --> 00:29:05,690
你一定会受到很多指责
You'll receive a lot of criticism too.

457
00:29:06,280 --> 00:29:07,910
徐律师负责的时候
When Mr. Seo took on the case,

458
00:29:07,990 --> 00:29:11,070
-他还曾被人叫做恶魔律师 -虽然
-he was called the devil's lawyer. -Well,

459
00:29:11,910 --> 00:29:13,620
我不是因为这种事退出的
that's not why I quit though.

460
00:29:14,240 --> 00:29:16,790
所以我来寻求你的帮助
I came here to see if I could get your help.

461
00:29:16,870 --> 00:29:19,750
只要不违法 我可以尽我所能
As long as there aren't any legal issues, of course, I can.

462
00:29:19,830 --> 00:29:22,210
你为什么要放弃辩护呢
So, why did you withdraw from the case?

463
00:29:25,630 --> 00:29:27,800
-千律师 -怎么了
-Mr. Cheon. -Yes?

464
00:29:29,930 --> 00:29:32,930
这个问题是不是有点无礼
Isn't that a bit rude?

465
00:29:34,140 --> 00:29:36,600
你没有事先预约就跑过来
You came here without an appointment.

466
00:29:36,680 --> 00:29:38,730
还直接问我为什么放弃辩护
Now, you're asking me why I withdrew from the case.

467
00:29:39,690 --> 00:29:41,360
是啊 你说得对
Yes, you're right.

468
00:29:41,440 --> 00:29:43,570
对不起 我向你道歉
I'm sorry. I'd like to apologize.

469
00:29:44,270 --> 00:29:46,030
我接受你的道歉
I accept your apology.

470
00:29:46,610 --> 00:29:48,950
你知道金敏宰主张无罪吧
You know that Mr. Kim is pleading not guilty, don't you?

471
00:29:49,990 --> 00:29:52,200
-是的 -他说这是他的父亲干的
-Yes. -He claims that his father did it

472
00:29:52,280 --> 00:29:54,280
并说他的父亲还活着 对吧
and that his father is still alive.

473
00:29:55,120 --> 00:29:56,040
没错
Yes.

474
00:29:56,120 --> 00:29:58,750
你也认为他的父亲还活着吗
Do you think his father is still alive too, Mr. Cheon?

475
00:30:02,540 --> 00:30:04,170
所以我才放弃的
That's why I withdrew.

476
00:30:06,510 --> 00:30:09,340
我只有相信他的父亲还活着 才能接手这个案子
I take on the case as long as I believe he's alive,

477
00:30:09,420 --> 00:30:10,720
但我无法相信
but I couldn't believe that.

478
00:30:11,220 --> 00:30:13,890
所以我对如何为他辩护毫无头绪
So, I couldn't figure out a way to defend Mr. Kim.

479
00:30:14,470 --> 00:30:15,350
不过
Anyway,

480
00:30:16,390 --> 00:30:19,560
你为什么要接这个案子
why are you thinking of taking on this case?

481
00:30:21,060 --> 00:30:22,600
因为我相信他的父亲还活着
Because I believe he's alive.

482
00:30:31,820 --> 00:30:34,530
你相信他的父亲还活着？谁说的
Do you believe he's alive? Says who?

483
00:30:34,620 --> 00:30:35,830
我说的
Says me.

484
00:30:36,410 --> 00:30:37,790
只是还没发现尸体而已
The body simply hasn't been found.

485
00:30:37,870 --> 00:30:41,160
任谁看都是金敏宰 杀害他的父亲后遗弃了尸体
It's obvious that Mr. Kim Minjae killed him and disposed of the body.

486
00:30:43,380 --> 00:30:45,710
你是实习检察官还是实习律师
Are you a probationary judicial officer or my probationary employee?

487
00:30:46,590 --> 00:30:48,840
我现在当然是实习律师
Of course, I am your probationary employee at the moment.

488
00:30:48,920 --> 00:30:52,010
你才工作两个月 就完全把他想成凶手了呢
You've only worked for two months, but you see him as the murderer.

489
00:30:52,090 --> 00:30:54,640
那万一明天就发现尸体了呢
What if the body is found tomorrow?

490
00:30:54,720 --> 00:30:56,010
-万一发现了呢 -没错
-If it's found-- -Yes.

491
00:30:56,100 --> 00:30:57,310
-万一发现了呢 -没错
-If it's found-- -Yes.

492
00:30:57,390 --> 00:30:58,560
不会被发现的
It won't be found.

493
00:31:04,860 --> 00:31:08,110
B A E K
B, A, E, K.

494
00:31:08,190 --> 00:31:10,030
这用韩语怎么读
How is that read in Korean?

495
00:31:10,690 --> 00:31:12,990
-白 -你姓什么
-Baek. -What is your last name?

496
00:31:14,740 --> 00:31:15,490
白
Baek.

497
00:31:16,330 --> 00:31:17,910
白法律事务所
Law Firm Baek.

498
00:31:18,580 --> 00:31:20,620
白玛丽
Baek Mari.

499
00:31:21,960 --> 00:31:23,120
你不会是…
Are you…

500
00:31:24,500 --> 00:31:25,580
唉唷
Well…

501
00:31:27,210 --> 00:31:28,960
这世上姓白的又不只有一两个
There are so many Baeks out there.

502
00:31:33,590 --> 00:31:34,800
还有谁
Who?

503
00:31:37,930 --> 00:31:39,680
-白种元 -还有呢
-Baek Jongwon. -And?

504
00:31:40,470 --> 00:31:41,480
-白智荣 -还有呢
-Baek Zyoung. -And?

505
00:31:41,560 --> 00:31:43,480
-白润植 -还有呢
-Baek Yoonsik. -And?

506
00:31:44,270 --> 00:31:45,440
还有？
And?

507
00:31:48,230 --> 00:31:49,270
白胜秀
Baek Seungsu.

508
00:31:49,440 --> 00:31:51,490
还有白胜秀啊 你看过《棒球大联盟》了吗
Oh, there's Baek Seungsu. Did you watch Stove League?

509
00:31:51,570 --> 00:31:52,610
当然了
Of course.

510
00:31:52,690 --> 00:31:55,530
那个超好看 但不知道为什么不出第二季
That was really good. I don't know why they aren't making season two.

511
00:31:56,200 --> 00:31:57,370
你也不知道为什么吗
Don't you know either?

512
00:32:01,660 --> 00:32:02,700
不知道
No, I don't.

513
00:32:05,580 --> 00:32:09,500
这张照片每次看都被帅到
You know, it looks so good every time I see it.

514
00:32:11,340 --> 00:32:12,210
把你放在这里
You can go here.

515
00:32:12,300 --> 00:32:15,010
徐民赫 检察官
PROSECUTOR SEO MINHYEOK

516
00:32:15,090 --> 00:32:16,510
爸
DAD

517
00:32:19,550 --> 00:32:20,640
喂？爸爸
Yes, Dad.

518
00:32:25,100 --> 00:32:26,980
是 父亲 有什么事吗
Yes, Father. What is this about?

519
00:32:27,400 --> 00:32:28,980
你在哪 在检察厅吗
Where are you? At the Prosecutor's Office?

520
00:32:29,060 --> 00:32:30,690
是的 我在把行李拿出来
Yes, I'm unpacking at the moment.

521
00:32:31,270 --> 00:32:32,570
下来一趟吧
Come downstairs.

522
00:32:32,650 --> 00:32:34,610
什么 你来这里了吗
What? You're here?

523
00:32:37,240 --> 00:32:38,490
徐检察官 你还好吗
Are you okay, Mr. Seo?

524
00:32:38,570 --> 00:32:40,080
401室 检察官办公室
ROOM 401, PROSECUTOR'S OFFICE

525
00:32:40,160 --> 00:32:41,160
我正在下去
I'm on my way.

526
00:32:48,540 --> 00:32:51,800
你知道枫津洞案吧
You know about the Pungjin-dong case, don't you?

527
00:32:53,670 --> 00:32:54,630
当然知道了
Of course.

528
00:32:54,720 --> 00:32:58,430
枫津洞怎么这么遭人热议
I keep hearing about Pungjin-dong. Why is it such a hot topic?

529
00:32:58,590 --> 00:32:59,680
你来负责吧
I want you to be in charge.

530
00:32:59,760 --> 00:33:02,890
你不是让我战略性地做选择吗
Didn't you want me to be strategic in my choices?

531
00:33:02,970 --> 00:33:04,140
我负责那件案子干吗
Why would I take that case?

532
00:33:04,220 --> 00:33:07,890
这是你一定能胜诉的案子 百分之百
You can win that case no matter what. No matter what.

533
00:33:07,980 --> 00:33:09,190
百分之百？
No matter what?

534
00:33:09,440 --> 00:33:13,030
凶器和尸体到现在都没有发现
They haven't even found the weapon used in the murder nor the body.

535
00:33:13,230 --> 00:33:14,650
他们很快就能找到的
I'm sure they'll find it soon.

536
00:33:15,240 --> 00:33:17,450
我会叫你负责会败诉的案子吗
Do you think I'd tell you to take a case you'd lose?

537
00:33:18,030 --> 00:33:21,030
而且千智勋接手了这个案子
Also, Cheon Jihun took this case.

538
00:33:22,280 --> 00:33:24,700
他刚刚和玛丽一起来过
He came by with Mari a while ago.

539
00:33:26,290 --> 00:33:29,170
白代表把玛丽送到那里 一定是有缘由的
I'm sure he had a reason for sending Mari there.

540
00:33:29,250 --> 00:33:31,210
你一定要打赢这起官司
