00:43:17,170 --> 00:43:19,420
人在死去的时候说的话叫什么来着
What do you call one's last words before they die?

707
00:43:20,210 --> 00:43:21,260
死亡信息吗
A dying message?

708
00:43:21,340 --> 00:43:23,590
没错 死亡信息
That's it. Dying message.

709
00:43:25,680 --> 00:43:27,430
戏可不是那么演的
That's not how you act.

710
00:43:27,510 --> 00:43:28,930
我还得给你们表演这个吗
Do I have to show you how to do this?

711
00:43:32,060 --> 00:43:35,810
秀妍 是敏宰…
"Suyeon, Minjae…

712
00:43:38,900 --> 00:43:41,570
没看到我就上去了 她也有可能想这么说啊
didn't see me and walked right by me." She might've said that.

713
00:43:42,150 --> 00:43:45,200
我堂堂一个律师怎么还要演戏 真让人害臊
Gosh, why does a lawyer even have to act? How embarrassing.

714
00:43:45,950 --> 00:43:48,990
最适合恶魔律师绰号的人就是你
You are the perfect person to be called the devil's lawyer.

715
00:43:49,490 --> 00:43:51,790
你去法庭那么说吧 看看人们会说什么
Try saying that in court and see what people say.

716
00:43:51,870 --> 00:43:53,500
对啊 人们会怎么说
What do you think people would say?

717
00:43:53,580 --> 00:43:54,830
你有点过分了
You went too far.

718
00:43:54,920 --> 00:43:57,880
不 我的意思是柳熙珠馆长的话
What I'm saying is that Director Yoo's last words can't be used

719
00:43:57,960 --> 00:43:59,380
没有作为证言的效力
as a testimony in court.

720
00:43:59,460 --> 00:44:03,380
而且重要的是我们还没有找到 在案件中使用的刀
Most importantly, we haven't even found the knife that was used.

721
00:44:03,470 --> 00:44:04,880
你们找到刀了吗
Have you found the knife?

722
00:44:06,140 --> 00:44:07,640
你怎么知道是刀
How did you know it was a knife?

723
00:44:08,220 --> 00:44:09,640
一般常用的不是刀吗
Don't people normally use a knife?

724
00:44:10,220 --> 00:44:12,770
是你刺的吧
You stabbed her, didn't you?

725
00:44:14,020 --> 00:44:18,190
所以你打算怎么证明金敏宰是无辜的
So, how are you going to prove Mr. Kim Minjae's innocence?

726
00:44:18,270 --> 00:44:20,900
刀还没找到 尸体也没被发现
The knife hasn't been found and there's no body.

727
00:44:20,980 --> 00:44:22,610
你打算一直这样赖账吗
Are those your only claims?

728
00:44:22,690 --> 00:44:26,160
白实习 检方为了证明 金敏宰的罪行 现在在做什么
Ms. Baek, what is the prosecution doing to prove Mr. Kim's guilt?

729
00:44:26,660 --> 00:44:30,870
我从刚才开始就一直在说 他们在找死去的金画家的尸体
I have been telling you that they are searching for Artist Kim's dead body.

730
00:44:30,950 --> 00:44:33,160
果然是得85分的人会回答的答案
That's certainly an answer from someone who got 85 points.

731
00:44:33,250 --> 00:44:35,080
那我们从现在起要做什么
Then, what should we do from now?

732
00:44:35,160 --> 00:44:36,420
-什么 -什么
-What? -What?

733
00:44:36,500 --> 00:44:38,210
-什么 -就是那个
-What? -That's it.

734
00:44:38,290 --> 00:44:40,670
作为金敏宰的辩护律师
As lawyers representing Kim Minjae,

735
00:44:41,380 --> 00:44:43,050
我们要找到活着的金画家
we need to search for the living Artist Kim.

736
00:44:43,970 --> 00:44:45,380
真是不可理喻
What on earth are you--

737
00:44:46,380 --> 00:44:48,590
我们要怎么去找金画家
How are we supposed to find him?

738
00:44:48,760 --> 00:44:51,760
所以我们先去见见熟悉金画家的人吧
That's why we should find someone who knows him well first.

739
00:45:00,310 --> 00:45:02,570
这辆车不能开得安静点吗
Can't this car go any more quietly?

740
00:45:03,320 --> 00:45:04,690
安全行驶
Good driving.

741
00:45:05,650 --> 00:45:07,160
你在说什么啊
What are you talking about?

742
00:45:09,320 --> 00:45:12,160
第一洗衣店

743
00:45:12,290 --> 00:45:13,790
那不是金秀妍吗
Isn't that Ms. Kim Suyeon?

744
00:45:14,120 --> 00:45:15,790
她给我来电话了
She's calling me.

745
00:45:16,460 --> 00:45:17,960
秀妍 我就在前…
Suyeon, I'm right up front--

746
00:45:18,040 --> 00:45:20,210
千律师 我这边突然有一个急救患者
Mr. Cheon, I have a patient that needs urgent care.

747
00:45:20,290 --> 00:45:21,460
我们恐怕要明天见了
We'll have to meet tomorrow.

748
00:45:22,340 --> 00:45:24,420
好的
Yes. Okay.

749
00:45:24,880 --> 00:45:27,720
我知道了 明天见
All right. See you tomorrow. Bye.

750
00:45:28,430 --> 00:45:29,890
怎么了 她在那里
What? She's right there.

751
00:45:29,970 --> 00:45:32,680
-你好… -不要喊 很奇怪
-Over here-- -Stop. It's suspicious.

752
00:45:33,180 --> 00:45:35,520
她说来了急救患者 要和我明天再见
She said she has an emergency patient and asked to meet tomorrow.

753
00:45:39,480 --> 00:45:40,350
藏起来
Duck!

754
00:45:42,440 --> 00:45:44,730
你就大声宣传我们在这里吧 她走了
Why don't you just tell everyone we're here? She's gone.

755
00:45:44,820 --> 00:45:46,440
我们跟她去看看急救患者是谁
Let's see who her emergency patient is.

756
00:45:48,570 --> 00:45:49,860
没问题
Okay.

757
00:46:23,980 --> 00:46:24,940
欢迎光临
Welcome.

758
00:46:28,950 --> 00:46:30,360
请问预约人尊姓大名
Under whose name is the reservation?

759
00:46:31,780 --> 00:46:34,160
我们今天来得太急 没有预约
Oh, we were in a rush so we couldn't make a reservation.

760
00:46:34,740 --> 00:46:37,290
我们店只在每月的第一周
During the first week of the previous month,

761
00:46:37,370 --> 00:46:40,710
接受下个月所有客人的用餐预约
we take reservations of all the guests who will come in the following month.

762
00:46:40,790 --> 00:46:42,420
今天能不能破例呢
Can't you make an exception for today?

763
00:46:42,920 --> 00:46:45,960
客人 我很抱歉 但还是请回吧
Ma'am, I'm terribly sorry, but would you please leave?

764
00:46:46,050 --> 00:46:47,260
你是这里的经理吧
You're the manager, aren't you?

765
00:46:47,510 --> 00:46:52,130
虽然这是机密 但我们其实正在进行调查
This is confidential, but we are actually doing an investigation.

766
00:46:52,720 --> 00:46:55,510
调查？那你是警察吗
An investigation? Are you the police?

767
00:46:57,140 --> 00:46:58,810
不 我是侦探
No, I'm a private detective.

768
00:46:58,890 --> 00:47:00,230
侦探？
A detective?

769
00:47:00,310 --> 00:47:01,520
那个…
Well…

770
00:47:18,080 --> 00:47:19,160
菜单
MENU

771
00:47:31,550 --> 00:47:33,680
她在等谁呢
Who is she waiting for?

772
00:47:34,340 --> 00:47:36,850
不知道 我们再等等吧
I'm not sure. Let's wait and see.

773
00:47:37,720 --> 00:47:41,520
不过这里氛围真好 我第一次来这种地方
By the way, it's really nice here. I've never been to a place like this.

774
00:47:41,600 --> 00:47:43,480
千律师 这种地方很贵吧
Mr. Cheon, isn't a place like this pricey?

775
00:47:43,560 --> 00:47:46,110
事务长 怪丢人的
Mr. Sa, stop embarrassing me.

776
00:47:46,440 --> 00:47:48,230
如果你不清楚 就像我一样装装样子
If you don't know, just go along with it like me.

777
00:48:06,880 --> 00:48:08,670
这是哪个国家的语言
What language is this?

778
00:48:08,750 --> 00:48:11,550
法国？白实习 你会说法语吧
French? Don't you know how to speak French, Ms. Baek?

779
00:48:14,180 --> 00:48:17,300
我会说英语 但法语就…
Oh, I speak a little English but not French.

780
00:48:19,680 --> 00:48:21,890
我们还是和那桌点一样的菜吧
Let's just ask for the same thing as that table.

781
00:48:21,970 --> 00:48:23,640
好 来份一样的吧
Okay. Ask for the same thing.

782
00:48:37,370 --> 00:48:39,370
晚间套餐只有这一种
There's only one dinner course.

783
00:48:39,950 --> 00:48:42,580
我们需要点主食
We have to pick the main dish.

784
00:48:43,080 --> 00:48:46,870
有牛排 鸭胸肉和羊排 我就点牛排了
There's steak, duck breast, and lamb chop. We'll go with steak.

785
00:48:46,960 --> 00:48:48,210
三个人都五分熟 没关系吧
Are we all okay with medium?

786
00:48:48,710 --> 00:48:50,460
搭配三杯红酒
Three wine pairings.

787
00:48:50,540 --> 00:48:54,090
甜点就要冰淇淋 白实习
And we'll have ice cream for dessert. Ms. Baek,

788
00:48:55,680 --> 00:48:56,680
请帮我转达
please pass that on.

789
00:49:13,030 --> 00:49:16,610
唉唷 最近的肉好老啊
Gosh, the meat is so tough these days.

790
00:49:30,460 --> 00:49:33,050
-喂 那个人… -那个人…
-Hey, that person is… -That person.

791
00:49:37,800 --> 00:49:39,430
她是住家帮佣韩才淑
She's the housekeeper, Han Jaesook.

792
00:49:39,590 --> 00:49:40,590
履历表 姓名 韩才淑
RESUME NAME: HAN JAESOOK

793
00:49:45,890 --> 00:49:48,060
-她俩在谈什么 -白实习 安静
-What are they talking about? -Hush, Ms. Baek.

794
00:49:48,690 --> 00:49:51,150
你安静点 我一点都听不清她们在说什么
Be quiet. I can't hear a thing they're saying.

795
00:49:52,690 --> 00:49:54,360
她们在聊什么呢
What do you think they're talking about?

796
00:49:54,440 --> 00:49:56,490
她见帮佣会有什么事呢
What does she have to talk about with the housekeeper?

797
00:49:57,400 --> 00:49:58,320
难道…
You don't think--

798
00:49:58,400 --> 00:50:00,110
难道是和案件有关的…
You don't think it's about the case, do you?

799
00:50:01,240 --> 00:50:03,530
难道他们在聊和案件有关的事情
You don't think it's about the case, do you?

800
00:50:23,100 --> 00:50:25,850
律师事务所 二楼
OFFICE OF LAW, 2F

801
00:50:31,440 --> 00:50:34,020
继兄妹 金秀妍 金敏宰 有力嫌疑人
STEP-SIBLINGS, KIM SUYEON, KIM MINJAE, PRIME SUSPECT

802
00:50:34,940 --> 00:50:36,650
金秀妍 26岁
KIM SUYEON, 26 YEARS OLD

803
00:50:37,230 --> 00:50:38,900
千智勋
CHEON JIHUN

804
00:50:41,110 --> 00:50:44,120
我们需要点主食
We have to pick the main dish.

805
00:50:44,740 --> 00:50:48,330
有牛排 鸭胸肉和羊排 我就点牛排了
There's steak, duck breast, and lamb chop. We'll go with steak.

806
00:50:50,460 --> 00:50:51,870
他到底是何方神圣
Who really is he?

807
00:50:58,920 --> 00:50:59,970
白实习
Ms. Baek.

808
00:51:01,760 --> 00:51:03,300
你不饿吗
Aren't you hungry?

809
00:51:03,390 --> 00:51:05,640
那种地方餐量本来就那么少吗
Do places like that usually give that little?

810
00:51:06,140 --> 00:51:08,180
法国人吃那么少怎么活
How do French people survive eating that little?

811
00:51:08,930 --> 00:51:09,810
我饿了
I'm hungry.

812
00:51:12,560 --> 00:51:15,610
我们应该吃炸酱面 偏偏吃了那种东西
We should've eaten jjajangmyeon. Why did we eat that?

813
00:51:16,190 --> 00:51:18,980
这么晚了你要去哪里 你怎么换衣服了
Are you going somewhere at this hour? Why did you change?

814
00:51:19,070 --> 00:51:20,820
我想去看一个地方
There's a place I want to check out.

815
00:51:21,320 --> 00:51:23,950
我换成了最方便活动的衣服
I changed into something that was more suitable to move around in.

816
00:51:25,830 --> 00:51:28,620
是吗 去哪
Okay. Well, where?

817
00:51:28,700 --> 00:51:32,080
我要去亲眼看看案发现场
I need to see the crime scene in person.

818
00:51:32,160 --> 00:51:33,330
什么
What?

819
00:51:33,920 --> 00:51:36,210
现在已经晚上11点了
At 11 o'clock at night?

820
00:51:36,960 --> 00:51:40,550
外面都已经这么黑了 你还要去哪里
It's so dark outside. Where do you think you're going?

821
00:51:40,630 --> 00:51:43,470
你们在开玩笑吗 我们走吧
Are you kidding me right now? Let's get going.

822
00:51:45,470 --> 00:51:46,640
从现在起
From now on,

823
00:51:47,930 --> 00:51:49,220
请叫我千侦探
call me Detective Cheon.

824
00:52:06,280 --> 00:52:07,280
还不走吗
Aren't we leaving?

825
00:52:07,580 --> 00:52:11,580
千智勋侦探 千侦探
DETECTIVE CHEON JIHUN DETECTIVE CHEON

826
00:52:16,250 --> 00:52:17,540
还不走吗
Aren't we leaving?

827
00:52:25,130 --> 00:52:26,180
千侦探？
Detective Cheon?

828
00:52:29,560 --> 00:52:31,220
小心有狗 禁止随意出入

829
00:52:50,450 --> 00:52:52,490
怎么了 你不是想来看吗 快走吧
Come on. I thought you wanted to see it for yourself.

830
00:52:52,580 --> 00:52:55,460
我的腿突然抽筋了
Wait. My leg is cramping up.

831
00:53:02,420 --> 00:53:05,090
千律师 你不走吗
Mr. Cheon, aren't you coming?

832
00:53:05,670 --> 00:53:07,550
晚上太黑了 我下次再来
It's too dark, so I'll come back later.

833
00:53:08,140 --> 00:53:09,180
你把墨镜摘了吧
Take those sunglasses off.

834
00:53:14,390 --> 00:53:16,100
那我们进去吧
Shall we go in, then?

835
00:53:51,720 --> 00:53:53,180
那个
Hey.

836
00:53:54,140 --> 00:53:54,970
这里
Here.

837
00:53:56,140 --> 00:53:57,560
怎么回事 好像没电了
I think the power went out.

838
00:53:58,230 --> 00:53:59,690
白天我们再来吧
Let's come back during the day.

839
00:53:59,770 --> 00:54:02,610
我完全没有预想到会没电
I didn't expect the power to be out.

840
00:54:02,980 --> 00:54:04,480
是我考虑不足
That was my mistake.

841
00:54:05,480 --> 00:54:06,820
你们别再开玩笑了
Stop messing around.

842
00:54:22,250 --> 00:54:23,920
呼吸声怎么回事
Why is he breathing like that?

843
00:54:44,230 --> 00:54:46,230
金敏宰真的不知道吗
Do you think Mr. Kim Minjae really didn't know?

844
00:54:46,780 --> 00:54:48,990
案发时如果家里很暗 而且他还喝醉了
If it was dark and he was drunk at the time,

845
00:54:49,070 --> 00:54:51,240
就无法排除他不知情的可能性
we can't rule out that possibility.

846
00:54:51,320 --> 00:54:53,240
你是因为自己是他的律师 所以在袒护他吗
Aren't you taking his side too much as his lawyer?

847
00:54:54,120 --> 00:54:55,990
我也觉得有可能
I think it is possible.

848
00:54:56,740 --> 00:55:00,040
金秀妍说她没有在房间里听到争吵声
Ms. Kim Suyeon said she didn't hear the fighting from her room.

849
00:55:01,000 --> 00:55:02,170
我们去确认一下
Let's check.

850
00:55:03,540 --> 00:55:04,670
事务长
Mr. Sa.

851
00:55:05,670 --> 00:55:06,750
我自己？
By myself?

852
00:55:09,010 --> 00:55:10,590
我不要
I don't want to.

853
00:55:10,760 --> 00:55:11,680
玛丽
Mari.

854
00:55:12,550 --> 00:55:13,760
什么
What?

855
00:55:16,510 --> 00:55:18,970
应该是想要确认的人上去看看吧
The person who wants to check should go upstairs.

856
00:55:19,060 --> 00:55:20,680
你上去吧
You should go, Mr. Cheon.

857
00:55:20,770 --> 00:55:21,690
不可以
No.

858
00:55:22,020 --> 00:55:23,230
-为什么 -我害怕
-Why not? -I'm scared.

859
00:55:24,480 --> 00:55:26,230
那我和事务长一起上去 可以了吧
I'll go upstairs with Mr. Sa, okay?

860
00:55:26,320 --> 00:55:27,820
-不可以 -为什么
-No. -Why not?

861
00:55:27,900 --> 00:55:28,860
那就只剩我一个人了
I'll be left alone.

862
00:55:28,980 --> 00:55:31,450
天啊 那我自己一个人上去 这样总行了吧
My goodness. Fine, I'll go upstairs by myself. Are you happy?

863
00:55:31,530 --> 00:55:32,570
可以
Yes.

864
00:56:03,140 --> 00:56:05,270
现在都几点了 你怎么才回来
Do you know what time it is? Why are you so late?

865
00:56:05,350 --> 00:56:07,650
偶尔也有可能啊 你管我干吗
It can happen. Why do you care?

866
00:56:07,730 --> 00:56:09,070
你这个家伙
You jerk!

867
00:56:10,570 --> 00:56:12,690
-妈 我… -白实习
-Mother, I-- -Ms. Baek!

868
00:56:13,110 --> 00:56:14,030
你能听见吗
Can you hear us?

869
00:56:16,370 --> 00:56:17,700
看来听不到
It doesn't seem like she can.

870
00:56:18,160 --> 00:56:21,200
白实习 如果听不到你就回答我
Ms. Baek, tell us if you can't hear us.

871
00:56:21,290 --> 00:56:23,910
她都听不到 怎么回答你
How can she answer you if she can't hear you?

872
00:57:03,410 --> 00:57:05,750
千律师 外面有人
Mr. Cheon, someone is out there!

873
00:59:13,790 --> 00:59:14,840
千律师
Mr. Cheon.

874
00:59:19,920 --> 00:59:20,920
待在这里
Stay here.

875
00:59:52,080 --> 00:59:54,960
《平价正义》
ONE DOLLAR LAWYER

876
01:00:28,030 --> 01:00:29,490
像金敏宰的主张一样
As Kim Minjae claimed,

877
01:00:29,580 --> 01:00:32,580
父亲杀害母亲后 消失的可能性…
the likelihood that his father killed his mother and disappeared is…

878
01:00:32,790 --> 01:00:35,290
金敏宰并非你的亲弟弟 你相信他所有的话吗
He isn't even your real brother. Do you believe everything he says?

879
01:00:35,420 --> 01:00:36,290
他连虫子也杀不了
He can't even kill a bug.

880
01:00:36,830 --> 01:00:37,580
是我杀的
I'm the one who killed.

881
01:00:37,880 --> 01:00:39,920
那会是金敏宰的真实面目吗
Is that Mr. Kim Minjae's true self?

882
01:00:40,000 --> 01:00:41,760
-你到底为什么那么做 -只有我感到奇怪吗
